                "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                "paragraphTitle": "NoFear",
                "paragraphSubtitles": ["Meet the players!"],
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Every week on No Fear, 20 players climb, swim and jump as they race to the finish line. Only three people make it to the final each week. In the end, there can be only one winner! Let's meet the three Meet the players! fastest people from last week …"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                "paragraphTitle": "Sam McGunn, 32",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Sam is a firefighter. He works hard, but in his free time he's really active. He's jumped out of an airplane seven times, and he's run 23 marathons! Sam is very fit, but he's never won a competition. That's why he wants to win this. His wife, Tara, and son, Ben, are here to support him. What do you think? Is Sam the strongest player on the show?"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                "paragraphTitle": "Hana Hansen, 28",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Hana hasn't played any sports in her life. But she owns a large farm and works on it seven days a week, 364 days a year. She often rides horses on the farm. Her husband, Raoul, spends a lot of time working in other countries, so she often has to take care of the animals, the house and their three young children on her own. Hana doesn't have any time for sports, but she's strong and she's a fighter. Can she beat Sam or Jude?"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                "paragraphTitle": "Jude Wexler, 31",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Jude doesn't work, but he's traveled all over the world. He's climbed mountains in Africa and raced cars in the Middle East. Jude doesn't believe in hard work, he prefers to have fun. ‘I travel all the time.' Have you ever flown an airplane? ‘I have. I loved it.' Have you ever been to a gym? ‘I haven't. I don't like exercising,' says Jude. ‘To prepare for this type of challenge, you should do what you love. And I love having fun. I believe I can win.' Jude has won 14 competitions with this method. Can he make it 15?"
                ]
              }
            ],
