                "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                "paragraphTitle": "SPOTLIGHT",
                "paragraphSubtitles": ["Karina Welch, ultra-runner"],
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Are you bored of running marathons? Do you want to try something new? Ultra-running is becoming more and more popular. Ultra-runs are longer than marathons. They are usually in remote and beautiful places, like the Gobi Desert or the Rocky Mountains, so you can run and enjoy nature at the same time!",
                  "This week, we're talking to Karina Welch, an ultra-runner, who is 66."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                "paragraphTitle": "So, Karina, when did you start running?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Twenty-five years ago, when I was in my late 40s. My children left home and I needed a way to spend my time, so I decided to start running. I began in my local park, then I ran a few marathons and finally I started ultra-running."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                "paragraphTitle": "How many ultra-runs have you done?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I've done around 20 races. My first run was in 2009 and it was really difficult. Ultra-runs are different from marathons, but they're better for your body. You normally run in the countryside and not on hard roads."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                "paragraphTitle": "Have you ever run a very difficult race? Where was it?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Yes, I have! Four years ago, I ran in the Marathon des Sables in the Sahara desert. I ran 250 km in six days, in very hot weather. I didn't actually run the whole time. I sometimes walked for a few kilometers, but that's normal in ultra-running. The important thing is to keep moving!"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 5,
                "paragraphTitle": "What do you do when you run for such a long time? Do you listen to music?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "No, I like the silence, especially when I'm running in a very quiet place. I like listening to the birds and the wind. I usually eat a lot when I run. You need food to keep your energy levels up."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 6,
                "paragraphTitle": "What are your tips for someone who is interested in ultra-running?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "It's never too late to start! I didn't run when I was young and now I love it. Start with jogging, and slowly increase the number of kilometers. And always warm up before you run!"
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 7,
                "paragraphTitle": "Finally, what do you like most about ultra-running?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I feel free. When I am running, I don't think about anything. It's just me, my legs and the sky."
                ]
              }
            ],
            "glossaryBox": [
              {
